{
  "doc_id": "9746",
  "text": "The dataset that was used in this study contains data collected by Cattane et al. [CITATION_1] , accessible at National Center For Biotechnology Information (NCBI) [13] Gene Expression Omnibus (GEO) database [CITATION_2] , with the accession number GSE62333. The dataset includes the gene expression of skin fibroblasts from 20 patients affected by SZ (mean age ± SD, 44.60 ± 12.67; 50% males) and 20 healthy control subjects (mean age ± SD, 48.40 ± 12.20; 45% males). The study involved patients who satisfied the DSM-IV criteria for SZ. The platform that was used for the microarray experiment was Affymetrix Human Gene 1.1 ST Array, which interrogates more than 28,000 well-annotated genes through UniGene or via Reference Sequence. This dataset was utilized for developing a classifier to distinguish the two classes.",
